<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2775: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mello
                                Franco</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chairman of the
                                Commission of Neutrals</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-11">January 11, 1933</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:33
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In reply to your telegram of the 2nd instant [<hi rend="italic">31st
                                ultimo?</hi>],<note n="24" xml:id="d162fn24"><ref target="frus1932v05#pg_218"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p.
                                    218</ref>.</note> I have the honor to state that the Brazilian
                            Government considers the proposal of your Commission acceptable, and is
                            disposed to collaborate with the states represented therein in any
                            action capable of leading the Governments of Bolivia and Paraguay to
                            reestablish a definitive peace.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Afranio de Mello
                            Franco</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>